# Local production reverse proxy for the trading dashboard.
#
#   https://personal-trading.agent  ->  the `pnpm start` server on 127.0.0.1:3000
#
# Coexistence with DDEV/Docker:
#   DDEV's router runs on ports 8080/8443 (see `ddev config global`:
#   router-http-port=8080, router-https-port=8443), so this binding of the
#   standard 80/443 does NOT conflict with DDEV. The only thing that would
#   reintroduce a clash is reconfiguring DDEV back onto 443.
#
# Served over plain HTTP on purpose: this is a loopback-only name (127.0.0.1
# via /etc/hosts), so TLS adds no security but a self-signed cert would trip a
# browser trust warning that can block the dashboard's own same-origin /api/*
# fetches. HTTP keeps it frictionless. (Server-to-external API calls — Alpaca,
# Robinhood, LLM CLIs — are made server-side and never touch Caddy regardless.)
#
# Usage:
#   1. one-time:  echo "127.0.0.1  personal-trading.agent" | sudo tee -a /etc/hosts
#   2. the app runs as a LaunchAgent on :3000; Caddy runs via `sudo brew services start caddy`
#   then open:  http://personal-trading.agent

http://personal-trading.agent {
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:3000
}
